Steps:

- [x] Once https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/pull/5988 is merged and deployed, QA against this record.
- [x] Figure out why this record is stuck in repairing status and fix.
Fixed the resource. Can a cloud fixity check against the resource and all of it's file sets as well as local fixity checks against all file sets.

```ruby
r = ChangeSetPersister.default.query_service.find_by(id: "1e544e7b-4566-439b-ab4f-b48d0585ee42")

r.member_ids.each do |id|
  CloudFixity::FixityRequestor.queue_resource_check!(id: id.to_s)
end

r.member_ids.each do |id|
  LocalFixityJob.perform_later(id: id.to_s)
end
```

researchdata.title: Trainings from Libcal Display Wrong Scheduled Time

comments.body:
I met with Sarah Reiff-Connell in PRDS and we talked through several issues: 

- [ ] The Trainings event feed on the homepage (https://researchdata.princeton.edu/) is still displaying in UTC.
- [x] The Trainings feed is also displaying with the latest workshop date first, instead of the most recent, which they would like to change. 
- [x] The Trainings feed on the homepage is displaying events not using the internal tag "Princeton Research Data Service," so I'm not 100% certain that our internal tag RSS feed from LibCal is working. 
- [x] We'd like the events on this page (https://researchdata.princeton.edu/events-and-training) to display the most recent first and to pull in from the internal tag feed as well. It doesn't matter if past events are displayed. 
- [x] Is there a way to pull in other campus groups' events into the PRDS website that isn't manual? (e.g. a feed from MyPU scheduler)
- [x] Sending others RSS feeds of PRDS events that they can pull into external calendars (probably the internal tag RSS would work for this) 

It would be great if we could take a look at this next week @kevinreiss.

@VickieKarasic I think the last issue are out of scope for the PRDS drupal system. Any other system could pull our guides feeds. ~~The last issue I see on the website looks to be formatted correctly. I did not manually correct it and the node itself has no edits in Drupal so maybe this is fixed?~~ Alas I misread it. It's just that this event is late enough in the day for the incorrect time to seem reasonable....

If there is another specific feed that has been identified that they want to pull in this can be done. Please open up a new ticket with the specific details. We can make it into the same content type if that is appropriate.

@kevinreiss I see what you mean about that event on 10/24, so looks like we still need to look into the UTC issue. 

Agreed about breaking out those other points about RSS feeds into new issues as they arise, so I think we are all set on that front with this ticket.

If we want to additional RSS feeds to the events calendar I think we can do that. Make a ticket for each specific one. I don't think the Drupal site is the place to push our own data out from though. We should do that directly from Springshare's feeds. I'm sure what Drupal would add to the equation in the context of exposing our data to the world via RSS.

Sounds good - we haven't gotten requests for specific feeds yet, but I will create new tickets if/when we do. And yes, I was thinking we'd share the RSS feed directly from LibCal with the internal tag for "prds" to any outside folks.
